<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880913-0025 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief: KMS Industries Inc. </HL><SO> </SO><CO> KMSI </CO><IN> BBK </IN><TEXT>   KMS Industries Inc., Ann Arbor, Mich., said it extended to Oct. 27 its $3-a-share tender offer to holders of fewer than 100 shares of the research and development concern.    KMS said the previously announced offer, intended to reduce the company's expense in handling small accounts, applies to stock of record June 30. The initial offer, made July 29, was scheduled to expire Thursday. KMS said its goal is to purchase 100,000 shares from about 10,000 shareholders.    In national over-the-counter trading yesterday, KMS shares closed at $3, unchanged. </TEXT></DOC>